In addition to face masks, there are also a large number of vacancies in protective products such as disinfectants, goggles and thermometers, according to the Hsinking newspaper. Ma Ling, general manager of Chengdu Zhongguang Detergent Co. , Ltd. , told the Beijing News that after the outbreak, the company began working overtime to produce disinfectant.

The full text is 2,455 words and takes about 5 minutes to read

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 28, according to the National Health Commission, 30 medical teams, totaling 4,130 people, have arrived in Hubei since January 24, when the first medical teams from Shanghai and Guangdong arrived in Wuhan. Affected by the epidemic in Wuhan, medical resources are being sent to Wuhan from all over the country. In addition to the medical team, a large number of masks, protective clothing, disinfectant and other related medical supplies are also on the way.

A Hsinking newspaper reporter recently interviewed a number of medical supply companies that were still working overtime during the Spring Festival, some of which had been working overtime to produce masks, medicines, protective clothing and so on. However, Chen Hua (not his real name) , a senior sales company in the medical industry, told the Beijing News that at present, for example, the price of face masks has increased more than five times, the market price has risen, and the merchants hold the pricing power.

━━━━━

Online off-line off off-line off-line off-line off-line, some people to stock up with cash transactions

"On January 22, the factory price for the masks was 0.3 yuan each, the next day it was 0.6 yuan each, the third day it was 1 yuan each, and now it's 1.5 yuan or 2 yuan each, " said Chen Hua, the owner of a medical sales company, he introduced to the Beijing News reporter usually disposable medical masks and surgical masks, the cost is about 0.3 yuan, with the development of the epidemic and time, the current wholesale price of masks has risen to 2 yuan.

Chen Hua told a reporter from the Beijing News that at present some manufacturers and wholesalers have the practice of driving up prices. Medical materials such as masks have become a seller's market. Some wholesalers and manufacturers have large stocks of masks and set their own prices, it's a lot more than it usually is. "I really can't stand it any more. " According to Chen Hua, at present, for example, a large number of transactions use cash, not the use of money transfer, but also rely on acquaintances to introduce, only resources.

Even though the price has gone up, the supply of face masks is still short of demand. On the afternoon of January 26, a reporter from the HSINKING newspaper searched 10 shops selling 3m face masks on Taobao and found that they were out of stock. At the same time, the line of some pharmacies, there are out of stock or long lines to buy masks.

Chen was shocked by the speed of the increase in mask prices, but said he had withdrawn from the market, providing only information about sales and not buying and selling.

"I would rather spend some money to give it away for free, but I don't dare to sell it. " Chen has his own medical materials manufacturer and sales company, with clients as distributors and a Terminal Hospital. Chen Hua said bluntly, the cost of masks in this circle is transparent, but now the factory price, regardless of whether they have raised the price, will make people feel that they earned a lot. Chen Hua also said that in addition to face masks, protective clothing and other materials also rise in price, "before selling 60 yuan a set of protective clothing, now an average of 200 yuan. ".

So far, eight hospitals, including the Hubei Provincial Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine, the Huakuta Union Hospital and the Hubei Provincial Children's Medical Center, have issued announcements one after another, collect and donate N95 masks, disposable medical masks, surgical masks and other protective materials from all walks of life. At the same time, the counties and cities around Wuhan have also made their own pictures to ask for help.

Call on relatives and friends to work overtime spontaneously, and double the number of employees who return to work within 3 days

"We started working 24-hour shifts on the 20th, with all of us working double shifts, " Ma said. In order to supply the disinfectant needed for the outbreak, Ma said the company offered canteens to employees who came back to work overtime, raising wages to ensure that they would not have to worry about working overtime. Ma Ling said that the Chengdu Zhongguang Detergent Co. , Ltd. had only 60 employees. In order to improve production efficiency, employees spontaneously called on relatives and friends to work overtime during the Spring Festival. The number of employees increased to 120 within three days, now we can produce about 30,000 bottles of disinfectant a day.

According to the People's Daily, on January 27, there was a shortage of protective materials in Wuhan Seven Hospital, a designated Treatment Hospital for Febrile Patients under the trusteeship of Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University. The head of the fever clinic in seven hospitals in Wuhan said that since the opening of the clinic on January 22, six consultation rooms have been opened for 24-hour consultation, and nine doctors have been arranged to serve outpatient patients at the same time, with an average of about 1,000 patients per day. Wuhan Seven Hospitals Medical Supplies Warehouse Staff revealed that clinical staff daily normal consumption of 1,000 protective masks.

Not only disinfectant production companies, there are drug companies also during the Spring Festival overtime work. Chen Xianming, assistant general manager of Covid-19, told the Beijing News that the company decided to stop taking vacation days and resume production of emergency drugs after Wuhan reported the outbreak of the disease.

"Some employees turned back directly on the highway after receiving the notice of resumption of labor, and some just got their luggage out of the car and loaded into the car for departure, " Chen said, adding that the company had issued three vacation notices in a row during the Spring Festival, including from January 15 to inform the Spring Festival holiday time; January 20 to resume production; January 21 to decide to cancel the holiday.

Ministry of Industry and Information Technology: Spring Festival holiday, limited production capacity

According to Wang Jiangping, Vice Minister of the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology, since January 23, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology has received a list of demands for four batches of materials from Wuhan, which roughly cover four major categories and more than 20 varieties, "Most of the supplies, should be able to meet the needs, but things like protective clothing, masks and so on are now very prominent. ".

Wang Jiangping explained that China is a big producer, but because of the Spring Festival holiday, production capacity can not be used. China has already had the Spring Festival holiday and resumed production by 40 percent. Products such as protective clothing are still hard to meet demand.

The Ministry of Industry and Information Technology (MIIT) said the list of requirements currently provided by Hubei Province is roughly 100,000 pieces of protective clothing for medical use every day, or 3 million pieces a month. The production capacity that meets China's standards is actually only permitted by 40 enterprises, distributed in 14 provinces. The total production capacity is actually only 30,000 sets of production capacity per day. So 40% of the resumed production can only reach a part of the production, so this contradiction is very prominent. In addition, China also has part of its export production capacity, which is about 50,000 sets of production capacity per day. This is for Europe and the United States to supply overseas. Without the permission of Chinese standards, this transformation takes a little time.

According to the official wechat account of the State Drug Administration, the State Food and Drug Administration has now focused on supervision and inspection of manufacturers such as medical protective masks, requiring local drug regulatory authorities to strengthen supervision and inspection of the production and circulation of drugs and medical devices, focusing on the supervision and inspection of biological products related to epidemic prevention and control, antiviral drugs, medical protective masks, medical protective clothing, suction machines and relevant in vitro diagnostic reagents, etc. , strengthen supervision and random inspection and adverse events monitoring. To carry out targeted supervision and inspection of pharmaceutical and medical device trading enterprises involved in epidemic prevention and control, focusing on the channels for purchasing and selling drugs, purchase and sale records, storage and transportation conditions and other contents, and urge enterprises to strictly abide by the norms for the quality management of pharmaceutical and medical device trading, ensure the traceability of pharmaceutical and medical devices.

Cheng Zijiao, a reporter for the Hsinking newspaper, an intern, editor of Zhao Fangyuan, Liu Xiaoyang, proofread Li Xiangling
